<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/220.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase,]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Say to the Minister for Foreign Affairs that there are objections to the
                            proposed convention, set forth in your July 28; and that before entering
                            into any convention it is highly desirable to make the preliminary
                            investigation, the result of which would probably compensate Ecuador
                            fully for the outlay. Ascertain whether in the absence of negotiation of
                            a convention the $8100 will be available.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>